radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated and fluid filled with fecalized material, measuring up to 1.9 cm in diameter. A calcification within the lumen proximally measures 0.9 x 0.9 cm compatible with an appendicolith. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, and rectum show no abnormalities.
